http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Pedestrian-killed-in-accident/article13995114.ece

A 61-year-old pedestrian, identified as Kochuraman of Kulathammal, near Kattakada, was mowed down by a mini lorry as he was trying to cross the road at the Overbridge traffic signal.According to the City Traffic Police, Kochuraman was attempting to cross the road even as the lights went green and the speeding lorry hit him.Though he was rushed to Government Medical College Hospital, he was declared brought dead.The body of Kochuraman, a labourer whose wife passed away a few years ago, has been shifted to the MCH morgue and will be handed over to relatives after autopsy on Tuesday.